This comic was the most expensive comic I’ve ever made to date to bring this to the community. I do understand people will be trying to resale and get as many copies as possible. So on my website each customer is limited to only 1 of each cover to keep it fair for the community.  Link in Bio!

Happy I’m not an “influencer” today after finding out instagram and facebook will not be paying people for reels anymore! What does this mean for influencers?!?!? All I know is I’m so glad that I spent the last 3 years building an actual business selling comics! I do have friends that make a living from reels and I feel bad because I know what it’s like to have your income suddenly shut off as it did for me and half the world back in 2020. I’m stronger now because of it, so I expect some strong people in the years to come because of this.

It’s official!!! Alice in Transylvania is now live on Kickstarter! This took a lot longer than expected but it was worth the wait. Such an amazing group of people worked on this with me. Ruben @rubennajera is always the best, we are pretty similar people and grew up almost the exact same way. He had a crazy good imagination just like me! Alex @alexsaviuk is such a legend he has worked on everything and might be most famous for his long run with Spider-Man! It was so cool to work with you Alex and now have Alice in Transylvania be part of your legendary work. I had to bring in Ryan @ryanm_kincaid as he just doesn’t miss or disappoint. Ryan’s work is top tier and has always been one of my favorite artist with his unique style. He really did bring Alice to life on this one.  Fernando @ferncord_art is a straight work horse and is always ready to spend countless hours day and night making sure everything is perfect. His interiors are amazing and if something isn’t right he goes back and make sure it’s just perfect with his team. Thank you everyone who has supported my Journey and I look forward to seeing where it goes! Link in bio 🎉

Proud to announce Alex Saviuk is part of the team. Truly a legend. @alexsaviuk For many of us Alex work has been in your collections for decades if your like me. Go grab Cover A for Alice in Transylvania. Link in bio
